title: For Sale:  Converted Saiga 12 guage shotgun w/all essential reliability parts, 4 Mags 1 drum,
location: Beltway 8 & westpark tollway, westchase area, Houston, Texas
postcontent:
Up for sale is a properly and fully converted Saiga 12 guage shotgun. Smithing work done by Elite Texas Armory. This saiga came out of the izhmash plant in Russia that still produces Kalashnikov pattern firearms today. It has every essential component installed for optimum receiver lifespan and reliability. For in depth information on this saiga, see below.

ASKING $1800 FOR EVERYTHING
 WILL ENTERTAIN REASONABLE OFFERS/PARTIAL TRADES. PLEASE NO LOWBALLING

Unfortunately these poor quality pics were taken from my phone as I do not currently have a better option. If you would closer or specific pictures please let me know and I will get them to you.

All after market parts are as follows:

- FOUR SGM tactical 10 round magazines (only 3 are pictured. Did not have handy at time of picture. Will update picture)

-ONE MD Arms 20 round drum (I've never had a failure to feed from this drum, only fits 2 3/4 shells)

-MD Arms v plug(variable gas plug with many gas valve settings to accomodate all types of ammunition)                   

-MD Arms piston

-Arsenal AK trigger group w/trigger guard screwed in

-DPH Arms internal stock adapter w/ DPH Arms Skeleton stock w/ a nice big rubber buttpad for comfort and ease of  firing

-Hogue AK monogrip(IMO most comfortable grip out there)

-Krebs custom hammer and trigger pin retainer plate(not the standard pain in the butt shepards crook)

-tromix shark muzzle brake

-rock solid CHAOS US extended quad rail with HK style sights(www.chaosus.com A fantastic rail made by an american with the perfect iron sights for a saiga).

-CAA foregrip
-I also have a bolt hold open kit included but it is not currently installed on the rifle. This link from carolinashooterssupply.com http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yek8AfLlu-s explains how to install the bolt hold open if you so choose. I never got around to installing it myself.

-factory original gas plug, piston, trigger group(will not fit this rifle anymore), factory bolt hold open, factory barrel thread protector. Also have the manual if desired)

ASKING $1800 FOR EVERYTHING, WILL ENTERTANY REASONABLE OFFERS/PARTIAL TRADES. PLEASE NO LOWBALLING

PARTIAL TRADES: SPECIFICALLY LOOKING FOR A KEL TEC PMR(will give $550 partial trade credit), FN FIVE SEVEN 5.7x28 pistol(will give $1250 partial trade credit).

This rifle has been very well taken care of and has had alot of work done. I personally would say it is on the higher end of the spectrum of converted saigas in terms of components used and work done(reliability). In the case of the saiga rifles, converted means it has been physically converted from its sporting rifle configuration(rifle stock, no pistol grip, standard trigger group) to the AK type configuration(AK configured stock, AK pistol grip, AK trigger group,). This is done by physically cutting the existing rifle stock tang and replacing it with an internal AK stock adapter as well as grinding/drilling(depending on your method) off existing pins/rivets.There are non conversion methods of attaching a pistol gripped stock, but in my opinion most tend to look and feel wonky due to the odd alignment of the stock to the receiver. There are many different ways to go about doing this conversion, not all of which are handled properly. This conversion was handled properly and its function attests to the work done. If you have any further questions or want to see more pictures please let me know.

Bolt carrier has had just a few touches to smooth out the action a bit, but most wearing in is still in the process as I've only had maybe 150 rounds max through it.

This rifle will cycle any ammunition you put through it given the proper gas setting. If you are unsure of how to operate the gas settings I can give very simple instructions as well as you can find them everywhere on the internet including MD Arms' website. The receiver does not have any deformitites from use and both front and rear trunions are in perfect shape. I have shot a wide mix of ammunition through this rifle with zero failures. I have run a few 3" 00 buckshot on the proper gas setting to see how it would handle, but primarily have only run 2 3/4 low and medium brass 00 buckshot and mixed birdshot. For 2 3/4 buckshot and birdshot, only a single setting is needed without worry of damage to your receiver or trunion. You CAN use 3" magnum loads, however it does put more stress on the receiver and the trunions so be aware of your gass settings for high powered ammunition.  

I also have this ad posted on Texas gun trader under the name francomatic. I assure you this is a legitimate and original ad.

title: For Sale:  Walther P38/P4
postcontent:
The P4 was the first variant of Walther's famed P38, a redesign to make the pistol conform to Germany's new requirements for police sidearms. The P4 barrel is cut back by 1 inch and the pistol is fitted with an automated firing pin safety and decock-only lever. Otherwise identical to the P38, the weapon is robust, accurate and well balanced and field stripping and maintenance are simple and rapid. The P4 uses a double action trigger design similar to that of the earlier Walther PPKs, and a loaded chamber indicator is also incorporated. The fixed-barrel design mechanism operates by use of a wedge-shaped locking block underneath the breech. As a fill-in, the P4 was actually superior to the P-38, and was popular with users. The P4 was only made from 1975 to 1981, with few commercial models imported into the US.

This pistol features synthetic grips, two 8-round magazines, holster, locking gun case with 2 locks and 2 keyed alike keys, original box, cleaning instructions and 9mm cleaning kit.  Its grips, metal, and bore are all in very good condition.
